OL,3,CBMA say GP's are 'not a priority' for
OL,4,CNesbitt after disputed funding contract
OL,6,FShe added: "Practices have been
OL,7,Fcollapsing around the minister and he
OL,8,Fhas chosen to ignore that.
OL,10,F"We can only reach the conclusion that
OL,11,Fgeneral practice is not a priority for
OL,12,Four minister."
OL,14,FWhen announcing his decision to
OL,15,Fimplement the contract, Mr Nesbitt had
OL,16,Fraised concerns over general practice
OL,17,Fsurgeries where patients are having to
OL,18,Fphone hundreds of times to get an
OL,19,Fappointment.
OL,26,@nD@LOUrD@AOUtD@NO]
