OL,3,CBMA say GP's are 'not a priority' for
OL,4,CNesbitt after disputed funding contract
OL,6,FDr O'Hagan said: "I fully understand
OL,7,Fthe frustration of patients, phoning a
OL,8,Fsurgery repeatedly only to be told
OL,9,Fthere are no appointments.
OL,11,F"Something we as GPs are desperate to
OL,12,Fchange, it is so frustrating to us
OL,13,Fthat this happens."
OL,15,FShe added: "The phone-in experience is
OL,16,Fa symptom of demand in general
OL,17,Fpractice and the lack of investment in
OL,18,Fcore funding to cope with this demand.
OL,20,F"We have been stressing this crisis
OL,21,Ffor over 15 years."
