OL,3,CBMA say GP's are 'not a priority' for
OL,4,CNesbitt after disputed funding contract
OL,6,FCommittee chair Philip McGuigan urged
OL,7,Fthe minister to re-engage with the BMA.
OL,9,FHe said: "We are all a bit shocked and
OL,10,Fdisappointed with what we heard (from)
OL,11,Fthe minister and the tone of his
OL,12,Fcommentary on Monday."
OL,14,FSpeaking to the media later on
OL,15,FThursday, Mr Nesbitt said there was no
OL,16,Fpoint denying that there was a problem
OL,17,Fwith access to GP services.
OL,26,@qD@JOUtD@VO]
